      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEBON STAR (2) hit the ground running from out wide and on speed early but faded and swamped late when 5th at this track in TG1-4W company. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Was a winner at her only start from this draw. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. KIM GOT GAME (7) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 4.5 lengths into second (20.29) at this track in a TG1-4W over 342m. Leading player again. SOUTH GIRLS (4) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing sixth at this track, but was among the placings at this track three back. Can turn it around this time. TAZ MANIAC (1) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to atone.",
